          "datePublished": "2023-07-10",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Keep one thing in mind, if you decide to join this school as a teacher, you'll be doing physical labour work a lot and working on things that doesn't come in your job profile. There is no Saturday off and they will even start bothering you to do useless work on a sunday. I already have experience in teaching so I refused to be their slave but if you're a junior teacher in their eyes they'd wanna harass you by making you overwork.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "JKG International School - Sector - 9,Vijay Nagar"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Nukra Chauhan"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-02-24",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I'm an ex student of JKG international school (passed out in 2012)  thanks to all my teachers, Principal mam and all other staff.\nThis school has a great management  experienced and professional teachers who are always ready to help their students in every expect .\nSpecial thanx to NEELAM MAM , KAMLESH MAM , ARCHANA MAM\n\nWe are four sisters and we all had studied from JKG school ,now my niece is also studying in this same  school..\nI am happy to see my school has indeed progressed a  lot new bunch of teachers and better facilities for the bright students..",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
